Prostomium bilobed, short, broad, wider than long (163 µm length and 355 µm wide); median antenna and eyespots absent. One pair of lateral antennae; short, small, conical and papillose. Palps posterior on prostomium with longitudinal folds. Pair of nuchal organs on the posterolateral margin of the prostomium (
Fig. 13C
). Peristomium fuse with prostomium, two pairs of short, conical, papillose tentacular cirri insert laterally (
Fig. 11A–C
). Dorsal tentacular cirri slightly shorter than ventral cirri.
